For the second part, we need to show that for any increasing sub sequence `l` of `nums`, its length is ≤ `lengthOfLIS (nums) (h_precond)`. This is true by the definition of `lengthOfLIS`. Since `lengthOfLIS` computes the maximum length of any increasing sub sequence, any other increasing sub sequence must have length less than or equal to this maximum.

