The `lengthOfLIS` function uses a dynamic programming approach where `dp[i]` represents the length of the longest increasing subsequence ending at index `i`. The recurrence relation is `dp[i] = max(dp[j] + 1)` for all `j < i` such that `nums[j] < nums[i]`.

